file=AI & Agents/anneal/operational/tool/anneal-tool-requirements.md · a—t:anneal — Tool Requirements=**This file specifies needs; it does not grant them.** Access is configured at deployment (operator/platform; Fleet Charter Rails 1–2 apply).\n · tb=\| Skill \| Needs \| Why \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| skill-lifecycle \| file read (all skills); file WRITE only post-board-approval, scoped to the approved diff \| apply approved revisions \| · tb=\| self-annealing-loop \| file read (post-mortems, ledgers); file write (own lessons ledger) \| intake + drafting \| · tb=\| prompt-context-engineering \| file read/write (Shared OS prompting-practices, post-approval) \| maintain shared discipline \| · tb=\| skill-quality-audit \| file read (fleet tree); script execution (skill_audit.py); file write (own reports) \| the sweep \| · a—t:anneal — Tool Requirements=anneal's write access is the most sensitive in the department — it is gated at TWO layers by design: board approval (process) and scoped write grants (runtime, relay's registry records it).\n